WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.920
Psalm 81, this evening, if you have your Bible with you,

00:00:02.920 --> 00:00:06.000
Psalm 81, and for a number of weeks now,

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:09.520
on Wednesday evening, we've been walking through this psalm.

00:00:09.520 --> 00:00:12.119
Of course, we started dealing with the fact

00:00:12.119 --> 00:00:13.859
that it is a psalm that was related

00:00:13.859 --> 00:00:16.760
to the Feast of Tabernacles and dealt with what that is

00:00:16.760 --> 00:00:20.360
and how that was important for the children of Israel

00:00:20.360 --> 00:00:24.239
to be mindful of God's deliverance and all that He did.

00:00:24.239 --> 00:00:27.120
And we've walked through the psalm in our last study.

00:00:27.120 --> 00:00:29.000
Of course, last week was prayer, praise, and pie,

00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:32.279
but prior to that, we looked at the end of verse number seven

00:00:32.279 --> 00:00:35.319
where the Lord said, I proved thee

00:00:35.319 --> 00:00:37.799
at the waters of Meribah, Sila.

00:00:37.799 --> 00:00:39.840
And we talked about that proving

00:00:39.840 --> 00:00:43.020
and how that God was challenging them,

00:00:43.020 --> 00:00:45.119
teaching them, proving them,

00:00:45.119 --> 00:00:49.119
and how that He'll prove you and I as well in our lives.

00:00:49.119 --> 00:00:51.919
As we move forward through the end of this chapter,

00:00:51.919 --> 00:00:53.959
just one psalm, of course, but it's interesting

00:00:53.959 --> 00:00:58.400
because in the final nine verses of Psalm 81,

00:00:58.400 --> 00:01:02.119
you will notice that the word hearken is used three times.

00:01:02.119 --> 00:01:04.199
And it's not always in the form of hearken.

00:01:04.199 --> 00:01:06.239
It's hearken or hearkened.

00:01:06.239 --> 00:01:09.739
But the reality is that three times in nine verses,

00:01:09.739 --> 00:01:11.779
we see that word.

00:01:11.779 --> 00:01:15.959
And these three references really provide a simple outline

00:01:15.959 --> 00:01:19.839
for the last nine verses of this particular psalm,

00:01:19.839 --> 00:01:22.580
and it will be for our next three lessons.

00:01:22.580 --> 00:01:25.800
And tonight, we'll deal with verses eight through 10.

00:01:25.800 --> 00:01:29.360
The title is this, wilt thou hearken?

00:01:29.360 --> 00:01:30.839
Wilt thou hearken?

00:01:30.839 --> 00:01:32.760
Next week on Wednesday evening,

00:01:32.760 --> 00:01:35.919
we'll look at the next couple of verses and deal with this.

00:01:35.919 --> 00:01:37.900
They hearkened not.

00:01:39.080 --> 00:01:41.160
Then as we finish up Psalm 81

00:01:41.160 --> 00:01:44.519
and we finish the last of these verses in that thought,

00:01:44.519 --> 00:01:49.519
the title for that message will be, what if they hearkened?

00:01:50.400 --> 00:01:51.480
And think about that.

00:01:51.480 --> 00:01:55.279
In these nine verses, we see the Lord speaking to his people

00:01:55.279 --> 00:01:57.360
and he says it this way,

00:01:57.360 --> 00:02:01.040
if thou wilt hearken unto me in verse number eight,

00:02:01.040 --> 00:02:03.519
and I've titled it, wilt thou hearken?

00:02:04.519 --> 00:02:06.319
And then we find and we understand

00:02:06.319 --> 00:02:08.240
as we'd read the Old Testament,

00:02:08.240 --> 00:02:12.160
that God will say next, they hearkened not.

00:02:12.160 --> 00:02:14.520
Isn't that a sad verse of Scripture

00:02:14.520 --> 00:02:17.360
to consider that God was giving instruction,

00:02:17.360 --> 00:02:21.080
he was giving what was good and beneficial for his people,

00:02:21.080 --> 00:02:23.800
but they would not listen, they would not hearken.

00:02:23.800 --> 00:02:26.479
And then we'll finish up, what if they had hearkened?

00:02:26.479 --> 00:02:29.199
What if they did, what do we miss out

00:02:29.199 --> 00:02:32.399
when we don't obey what God tells us to do?

00:02:32.399 --> 00:02:33.960
And we'll look at this as we study

00:02:33.960 --> 00:02:36.100
throughout the remainder of this year.

00:02:36.100 --> 00:02:38.919
The word hearken means to attend, it means to regard,

00:02:38.919 --> 00:02:42.360
it means to give heed to what is uttered,

00:02:42.360 --> 00:02:44.699
to observe or to obey.

00:02:44.699 --> 00:02:46.979
The children of Israel are familiar with this word

00:02:46.979 --> 00:02:49.000
in Deuteronomy chapter four, you don't need to turn there,

00:02:49.000 --> 00:02:51.619
I'll just read it and come right back to Psalm 81.

00:02:51.619 --> 00:02:54.779
But as the Lord is preparing his people

00:02:54.779 --> 00:02:56.380
for entrance into the land,

00:02:56.380 --> 00:02:59.820
Moses says to them in Deuteronomy four and verse one,

00:02:59.820 --> 00:03:02.360
now therefore hearken, O Israel,

00:03:02.360 --> 00:03:04.259
under the statutes and under the judgments

00:03:04.259 --> 00:03:06.759
which I teach you for to do them,

00:03:06.759 --> 00:03:09.779
that ye may live and go in and possess the land

00:03:09.779 --> 00:03:13.059
which the Lord God of your fathers giveth you.

00:03:13.059 --> 00:03:15.259
And so as we look at the text of Scripture this evening

00:03:15.259 --> 00:03:16.360
in verses eight through 10,

00:03:16.360 --> 00:03:19.740
notice the Bible says, hear, O my people,

00:03:19.740 --> 00:03:23.520
and I will testify unto thee, O Israel,

00:03:23.520 --> 00:03:26.419
if thou wilt hearken unto me,

00:03:26.419 --> 00:03:29.500
there shall no strange God be in thee,

00:03:29.500 --> 00:03:33.139
neither shalt thou worship any strange God.

00:03:33.139 --> 00:03:34.619
I am the Lord thy God,

00:03:34.619 --> 00:03:37.220
which brought thee out of the land of Egypt,

00:03:37.220 --> 00:03:40.580
open thy mouth wide, and I will fill it.

00:03:40.580 --> 00:03:42.380
As we consider the thought this evening,

00:03:42.380 --> 00:03:45.699
wilt thou hearken, four simple thoughts for you

00:03:45.699 --> 00:03:47.419
from these few verses of Scripture.

00:03:47.419 --> 00:03:50.419
Number one, the Lord instructs.

00:03:50.419 --> 00:03:52.979
Aren't you thankful that God gives instruction?

00:03:52.979 --> 00:03:56.139
You know, we are a blessed and privileged group of people

00:03:56.139 --> 00:03:57.500
to have a Bible.

00:03:58.460 --> 00:04:01.500
It's a unique privilege that we have.

00:04:01.500 --> 00:04:04.059
We understand that here in the midst of verse number eight,

00:04:04.059 --> 00:04:07.839
notice the Lord says, hear, O my people,

00:04:07.839 --> 00:04:12.839
notice this, and I will testify unto thee,

00:04:13.839 --> 00:04:17.600
if, O Israel, if thou wilt hearken unto me.

00:04:17.600 --> 00:04:19.160
In that middle phrase, when he says,

00:04:19.160 --> 00:04:20.760
I will testify unto thee,

00:04:20.760 --> 00:04:24.899
the word testify means to make a solemn declaration,

00:04:24.899 --> 00:04:28.980
whether verbal or written, to establish some fact.

00:04:28.980 --> 00:04:30.760
It carries with it this idea,

00:04:30.760 --> 00:04:35.760
to give testimony for the purpose of communicating to others

00:04:36.959 --> 00:04:41.760
a knowledge of something not known to them.

00:04:41.760 --> 00:04:44.399
Now think about that just for a second with me,

00:04:44.399 --> 00:04:47.440
that God is saying, as he's speaking to his people,

00:04:47.440 --> 00:04:49.600
I will testify unto thee.

00:04:49.600 --> 00:04:52.179
I'm going to communicate something to you

00:04:52.179 --> 00:04:54.200
that is beneficial for you,

00:04:54.200 --> 00:04:57.200
something that is not known by you,

00:04:57.200 --> 00:05:00.059
and I'm going to give that to you.

00:05:00.059 --> 00:05:03.059
I'm gonna testify, I'm going to instruct.

00:05:03.059 --> 00:05:05.440
I think about the truth in Psalm 68,

00:05:05.440 --> 00:05:07.720
just a few pages back in your Bible,

00:05:07.720 --> 00:05:11.519
the Bible says this in verse number 11 of Psalm 68,

00:05:12.440 --> 00:05:16.040
the Lord gave the word,

00:05:16.040 --> 00:05:17.359
and it continues and says,

00:05:17.359 --> 00:05:20.320
great was the company of those that published it,

00:05:20.320 --> 00:05:22.260
but I want you to consider that first phrase,

00:05:22.260 --> 00:05:24.140
the Lord gave the word.

00:05:24.140 --> 00:05:27.359
I'm thankful for the instruction that God has given to us.

00:05:27.359 --> 00:05:29.600
I'm thankful that all scripture

00:05:29.600 --> 00:05:31.640
is given by inspiration of God,

00:05:31.640 --> 00:05:35.000
and we tonight, as we look at this passage of scripture

00:05:35.000 --> 00:05:37.839
to consider that thought, wilt thou hearken,

00:05:37.839 --> 00:05:40.220
that we find that God says to his people,

00:05:40.220 --> 00:05:44.480
hear, O my people, and I will testify unto thee.

00:05:44.480 --> 00:05:47.799
He was telling them, I'm going to give you something

00:05:47.799 --> 00:05:50.920
that you don't know that is beneficial for you,

00:05:50.920 --> 00:05:53.799
that is advantageous that you know this.

00:05:53.799 --> 00:05:56.000
Hold your spot here in the book of Psalms

00:05:56.000 --> 00:05:58.880
and turn over quickly to the book of Romans, if you will,

00:05:58.880 --> 00:06:00.320
as we consider the New Testament,

00:06:00.320 --> 00:06:03.320
we think about this truth in Romans chapter three,

00:06:04.279 --> 00:06:06.600
we consider that God in Psalm 81,

00:06:06.600 --> 00:06:11.279
obviously is speaking to his people, his children,

00:06:11.279 --> 00:06:13.480
the people of Israel,

00:06:13.480 --> 00:06:17.600
and we find that today, as we look at us as New Testament

00:06:17.600 --> 00:06:21.179
church and understanding that God has given to us

00:06:21.179 --> 00:06:23.040
the whole canon of scripture,

00:06:23.040 --> 00:06:24.559
but in Romans chapter number three,

00:06:24.559 --> 00:06:27.940
there's an interesting aspect in which we notice,

00:06:27.940 --> 00:06:30.440
we open up into this chapter,

00:06:30.440 --> 00:06:33.279
thinking about even what is said there in Psalm 81

00:06:34.119 --> 00:06:37.920
with regard to the Lord testifying unto his people.

00:06:37.920 --> 00:06:41.359
Notice, if you will, in Romans three, in verse number one,

00:06:41.359 --> 00:06:45.239
the Bible says, what advantage then hath the Jew?

00:06:45.239 --> 00:06:48.600
Or what profit is there of circumcision?

00:06:48.600 --> 00:06:51.799
Now, you know, we've spent time on this in the past

00:06:51.799 --> 00:06:53.239
that throughout the New Testament,

00:06:53.239 --> 00:06:56.279
there's readily used the term circumcision

00:06:56.279 --> 00:06:59.720
to refer to Jews and the term uncircumcision

00:06:59.720 --> 00:07:01.320
to refer to Gentiles.

00:07:01.320 --> 00:07:03.040
And so here in verse number one,

00:07:03.799 --> 00:07:05.119
he's asking these questions twofold,

00:07:05.119 --> 00:07:06.359
what is the profit?

00:07:06.359 --> 00:07:08.480
What is the advantage of being a Jew?

00:07:08.480 --> 00:07:11.239
And then notice what the Bible says in verse number two,

00:07:11.239 --> 00:07:13.799
much every way, chiefly,

00:07:13.799 --> 00:07:17.179
notice, because that unto them

00:07:17.179 --> 00:07:21.480
were committed the oracles of God.

00:07:21.480 --> 00:07:24.359
You know, the children of Israel in Old Testament,

00:07:24.359 --> 00:07:26.760
obviously, God's dealing with his people,

00:07:26.760 --> 00:07:31.000
he committed to them, he gave them his word,

00:07:31.000 --> 00:07:34.480
and he's instructing them, he's teaching them,

00:07:34.480 --> 00:07:36.339
and he's giving to them,

00:07:36.339 --> 00:07:39.040
as we noted in Psalm 81 in verse number eight,

00:07:39.040 --> 00:07:41.720
he's providing, communicating to them

00:07:41.720 --> 00:07:46.279
something that is unknown to them, but will benefit them.

00:07:46.279 --> 00:07:49.359
And it's important that we understand this evening

00:07:49.359 --> 00:07:51.600
that we have the whole Bible,

00:07:51.600 --> 00:07:54.600
and God has given to us his word.

00:07:54.600 --> 00:07:56.519
And as we consider this evening,

00:07:56.519 --> 00:07:57.959
that the Lord instructs,

00:07:57.959 --> 00:08:00.480
and we even ask the question that is asked here

00:08:01.000 --> 00:08:01.839
in verse number eight,

00:08:01.839 --> 00:08:06.359
wilt thou hearken, if thou wilt hearken unto me?

00:08:06.359 --> 00:08:08.959
Will we hear, will we take heed to,

00:08:08.959 --> 00:08:13.579
will we give regard, will we desire and determine

00:08:13.579 --> 00:08:16.959
that we will observe or obey God's word as we hear it,

00:08:16.959 --> 00:08:21.799
understanding that God's word is instruction for us.

00:08:21.799 --> 00:08:24.480
Notice, not only do we see the Lord instructs,

00:08:24.480 --> 00:08:29.239
but we find in verse number nine that the Lord warns.

00:08:29.799 --> 00:08:33.119
I believe that it's necessary that God's people

00:08:33.119 --> 00:08:37.320
learn to appreciate the warnings that God gives in his word.

00:08:38.320 --> 00:08:42.340
The reality is that God's word is full of warnings.

00:08:42.340 --> 00:08:46.119
Warnings are given so that we can take heed to them,

00:08:46.119 --> 00:08:51.119
hearken unto them, so that we can avoid some adverse result

00:08:51.679 --> 00:08:56.280
or with regard to disobeying that warning

00:08:56.280 --> 00:08:59.159
or taking no concern for it,

00:09:00.039 --> 00:09:02.280
the consequences often are grave.

00:09:02.280 --> 00:09:03.760
The Bible says in verse number nine,

00:09:03.760 --> 00:09:07.080
as we think specifically of the warning that is given here,

00:09:07.080 --> 00:09:11.919
notice God says there shall no strange God be in thee,

00:09:13.080 --> 00:09:18.080
neither shalt thou worship any strange God.

00:09:18.500 --> 00:09:21.799
Uses the phrase strange God twice in verse number nine,

00:09:21.799 --> 00:09:24.080
and you know as well as I do,

00:09:24.080 --> 00:09:26.659
as we would study through the Old Testament,

00:09:26.659 --> 00:09:29.539
that idolatry was something that the children of Israel

00:09:29.539 --> 00:09:30.940
dealt with regularly.

00:09:30.940 --> 00:09:34.679
It was something that they constantly were seeming

00:09:34.679 --> 00:09:38.340
to go after strange gods and false gods.

00:09:38.340 --> 00:09:41.179
And we find that serving idols would bring judgment

00:09:41.179 --> 00:09:43.739
and God's delivering that warning,

00:09:43.739 --> 00:09:47.140
God's helping his people to understand

00:09:47.140 --> 00:09:51.580
that you should have no strange God within you,

00:09:51.580 --> 00:09:53.659
that there shall no strange God be in thee,

00:09:53.659 --> 00:09:58.460
neither shalt thou worship any strange God.

00:09:58.460 --> 00:10:00.260
That's unfortunate, we understand.

00:10:00.260 --> 00:10:03.080
and as we study through the Old Testament,

00:10:03.080 --> 00:10:06.820
that they regularly had no regard

00:10:06.820 --> 00:10:09.700
for this type of warning that God gave.

00:10:09.700 --> 00:10:11.780
In fact, as you think about the warnings,

00:10:11.780 --> 00:10:14.460
turn over to Psalm 19, if you will.

00:10:14.460 --> 00:10:18.940
And I want you to notice within the context of Psalm 19

00:10:18.940 --> 00:10:21.620
and speaking about the law of the Lord

00:10:21.620 --> 00:10:24.920
and how wonderful God's word is,

00:10:24.920 --> 00:10:29.200
the Bible in that text talks about being warned.

00:10:29.200 --> 00:10:34.200
And again, warnings are given for our benefit.

00:10:34.860 --> 00:10:37.660
We find in verse number 11 of Psalm 19,

00:10:37.660 --> 00:10:38.500
notice the Bible says,

00:10:38.500 --> 00:10:40.180
"'Moreover, by them.'"

00:10:40.180 --> 00:10:41.020
By what?

00:10:41.020 --> 00:10:42.860
Well, by the law of the Lord,

00:10:42.860 --> 00:10:44.300
the statutes of the Lord,

00:10:44.300 --> 00:10:45.860
the commandments of the Lord.

00:10:45.860 --> 00:10:50.860
He says, "'Moreover, by them is thy servant warned,

00:10:51.260 --> 00:10:55.880
"'and in keeping of them there is great reward.'"

00:10:56.740 --> 00:11:00.420
This evening, as much as we find that God instructs,

00:11:00.420 --> 00:11:02.940
we also find that God warns.

00:11:02.940 --> 00:11:04.460
And God gives us warnings.

00:11:04.460 --> 00:11:08.260
He gives you warnings and His word is full of warnings.

00:11:08.260 --> 00:11:11.460
And it's important even as I preached on Sunday evening

00:11:11.460 --> 00:11:13.940
when the Lord asked the question,

00:11:13.940 --> 00:11:14.980
"'Have you not read?'

00:11:14.980 --> 00:11:17.260
It's important that we're daily,

00:11:17.260 --> 00:11:19.220
regularly in God's word.

00:11:19.220 --> 00:11:20.040
Why?

00:11:20.040 --> 00:11:21.940
So that we can receive the instruction

00:11:21.940 --> 00:11:23.080
that God has for us,

00:11:23.100 --> 00:11:25.940
but also so that we can receive the warnings

00:11:25.940 --> 00:11:28.300
that God has for us.

00:11:28.300 --> 00:11:31.740
I know that you have, no doubt in my mind,

00:11:31.740 --> 00:11:33.680
you have materials in your home.

00:11:33.680 --> 00:11:36.340
We have things here in our church

00:11:36.340 --> 00:11:39.980
that have labels on them that are called warning labels.

00:11:39.980 --> 00:11:42.660
And oftentimes there are warning labels

00:11:42.660 --> 00:11:46.740
that may be on cleaning chemicals and solutions

00:11:46.740 --> 00:11:47.720
and what have you.

00:11:47.720 --> 00:11:50.660
And there's certain instructions and warning

00:11:50.660 --> 00:11:54.280
with regard to inhaling in a closed in area

00:11:54.280 --> 00:11:58.120
and the adverse effects that could come upon you.

00:11:58.120 --> 00:12:01.280
Having irritant on your skin with certain chemicals

00:12:01.280 --> 00:12:04.320
that you work with and all of that ingesting.

00:12:04.320 --> 00:12:07.680
If you ever have a child that you try to make sure

00:12:07.680 --> 00:12:10.760
those cleaning supplies are locked up and unavailable.

00:12:10.760 --> 00:12:11.580
Why?

00:12:11.580 --> 00:12:14.340
Because you don't want that child to consume

00:12:14.340 --> 00:12:16.800
those particular items.

00:12:16.800 --> 00:12:17.640
Why?

00:12:17.640 --> 00:12:18.840
Because there's a danger.

00:12:18.840 --> 00:12:23.360
Somebody, the FDA requires that there are warning labels

00:12:23.360 --> 00:12:24.560
on things that are sold.

00:12:24.560 --> 00:12:26.380
Now, some of the warning labels are kind of like

00:12:26.380 --> 00:12:27.300
you scratch your head and say,

00:12:27.300 --> 00:12:30.240
really you order hot coffee at McDonald's

00:12:30.240 --> 00:12:33.440
and it says warning contents may be hot.

00:12:33.440 --> 00:12:35.120
And you say, well, I hope they are.

00:12:35.120 --> 00:12:36.800
If they're not, I want a refund.

00:12:36.800 --> 00:12:39.480
I want something that's hot.

00:12:39.480 --> 00:12:42.560
But you understand that long ago,

00:12:42.560 --> 00:12:46.800
somebody sued them because they got burnt with hot coffee

00:12:46.800 --> 00:12:48.400
and got a large settlement.

00:12:48.920 --> 00:12:50.880
And now they put that warning on there.

00:12:50.880 --> 00:12:54.720
But we find this evening that God has given to us warnings

00:12:54.720 --> 00:12:57.520
and it's so important, the children of Israel,

00:12:57.520 --> 00:13:01.680
they're here in this situation and God is providing them

00:13:01.680 --> 00:13:03.400
with all that they need.

00:13:03.400 --> 00:13:06.860
We find the Lord instructs, we find that the Lord warns.

00:13:06.860 --> 00:13:09.840
Then I want you to notice as we get into verse number 10,

00:13:09.840 --> 00:13:12.400
notice what the Bible says here in verse number 10.

00:13:12.400 --> 00:13:16.160
Number three, if you're taking notes, the Lord reminds.

00:13:16.160 --> 00:13:19.880
The Bible says this, I am the Lord thy God,

00:13:19.880 --> 00:13:24.280
which brought thee out of the land of Egypt.

00:13:24.280 --> 00:13:27.660
As we just ponder the first half of verse number 10,

00:13:27.660 --> 00:13:30.360
consider with me how the Lord reminds them

00:13:30.360 --> 00:13:31.880
of some very important truth.

00:13:31.880 --> 00:13:34.640
Number one, he reminds them of who he is.

00:13:34.640 --> 00:13:37.380
I am the Lord thy God.

00:13:37.380 --> 00:13:39.400
I hope this evening that you understand

00:13:39.400 --> 00:13:42.920
that as you've been saved by the grace of God

